{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"95218223-154d-429b-aac0-af41fbe82ee1","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/post-merge-integrity-check/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/post-merge-integrity-check/tasks.md","title":"failedStep hardcodes '(main)' instead of dynamic baseBranch","rationale":"T-02 specifies failedStep as the literal string 'post-merge integrity check (main)'. For repos whose base branch is not 'main' (e.g. 'develop'), the escalation label will be misleading. recommendedAction already uses <baseBranch> dynamically, creating an inconsistency within the same escalation block."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/post-merge-integrity-check/tasks.md","title":"No explicit test task for config schema validation of archive.postMergeVerify","rationale":"T-01 lists acceptance criteria (non-array rejected, empty-string element rejected, absent key OK) but no test task explicitly covers these cases. They are exercised indirectly only if existing schema test infrastructure covers new fields automatically, which is not guaranteed."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/post-merge-integrity-check/design.md","title":"SHA race condition on concurrent merges is acknowledged and acceptable","rationale":"D3 notes that origin/<baseBranch> tip after fetch could point to a different concurrent merge's commit. The mitigation — reporting the SHA as 'the merge SHA at the time of verification' — is honest and sufficient for serial archive usage patterns."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/post-merge-integrity-check/design.md","title":"{ ok: true } return on infrastructure failure is semantically correct given the warning","rationale":"D6's choice to return { ok: true } on fetch/worktree-add failure with a stderrWrite warning is correct